ce:section.ce:para:
At present, the problem of iodine pollution is becoming increasingly serious and needs to be solved urgently. CTF-DB-MA with large specific surface area and containing heteroatoms N and S was synthesized with high iodine adsorption rate. The capture of iodine vapor was calculated by gravimetry in the experimental procedure described in SI. CTF-DB-MA (10 mg) and a large amount of iodine were weighed and the adsorption experiment was carried out at 75 ℃ atmospheric pressures. As shown in Fig. 4
                        a, CTF-DB-MA could realize the saturation adsorption of iodine vapor within 20 h, and the maximum adsorption amount of iodine was 2255.81 mg/g. The adsorption capacity of this polymer for iodine vapor is not lower than most of the previously reported polymers and is even comparable to some polymers with high iodine adsorption capacity (Table S2). The adsorption kinetics of iodine by CTF-DB-MA conformed to a pseudo-second-order kinetic model with a high fitting coefficient (R2 > 0.98) (Table 1
                        ). At the same time, the color of CTF-DB-MA changed from light yellow to reddish brown (Fig. 4a), indicating that CTF-DB-MA reacted with iodine. CTF-DB-MA with adsorbed I2 was exposed to air at room temperature and atmospheric pressure for retention experiments. As shown in Fig. S5, the weight of I2@CTF-DB-MA remained essentially unchanged for one week after adsorption of iodine vapor, indicating that there is an interaction between CTF-DB-MA and iodine vapor, and that the iodine vapor is not just attached to the pores of the material [41].

Raman spectroscopy was used to investigate whether CTF-DB-MA had charge transfer during the adsorption of iodine (Fig. 8
                        ). Before adsorption of I2, the Raman spectrum of CTF-DB-MA had a peak only at 1766.90 cm−1. However, after trapping I2, two characteristic peaks of I2@CTF-DB-MA were observed at 1768.27 cm−1 and 3048.61 cm−1. Whereas, after adsorption of iodine in hexane solution, I3
                        −@CTF-DB-MA observed three characteristic peaks at 667.32 cm−1, 1769.64 cm−1 and 3065.05 cm−1. This indicates that CTF-DB-MA interacts with iodine molecules and iodide ions and induces the formation of polyiodide anions [49]. This further confirms that the adsorption is formed through charge transfer interactions between CTF-DB-MA and iodine.
